1
00:00:03,860 --> 00:00:05,280
Thank you guys for having us over.

2
00:00:05,860 --> 00:00:07,980
Yeah, this is fun, couples night.

3
00:00:08,030 --> 00:00:09,470
I don't know why we don't hang out...

4
00:00:09,520 --> 00:00:10,980
...with married couples more often.

5
00:00:11,030 --> 00:00:12,680
Because every time we do...

6
00:00:12,730 --> 00:00:14,140
...you make jokes about swinging

7
00:00:14,190 --> 00:00:15,380
and scare them away.

8
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:18,690
You mean that Portuguese couple?

9
00:00:18,740 --> 00:00:20,690
Yeah, like you wouldn't have done it.

10
00:00:23,040 --> 00:00:25,680
Hey, you guys, I have great news.

11
00:00:25,730 --> 00:00:27,780
We're kind of in the middle of dinner.

12
00:00:27,830 --> 00:00:30,620
Oh, well, I already ate, but sure.

13
00:00:32,880 --> 00:00:34,480
Guess what happened at work today.

14
00:00:34,530 --> 00:00:36,850
A dinosaur died a million years ago?

15
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:41,260
Try 65 million years ago. And then try...

16
00:00:42,990 --> 00:00:45,310
My tenure review board met today,

17
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:47,600
and I hear it's looking really good.

18
00:00:48,130 --> 00:00:49,810
Yeah, do you have any idea

19
00:00:49,860 --> 00:00:51,300
what this means in academic circles?

20
00:00:51,350 --> 00:00:53,590
I am gonna get laid.

21
00:00:56,120 --> 00:00:57,910
- Hi, you guys. - Hey.

22
00:00:58,140 --> 00:00:59,390
Oh, ltalian.

23
00:01:00,110 --> 00:01:02,370
No one-- No one wanted seconds, right?

24
00:01:02,420 --> 00:01:03,830
No, I'm good.

25
00:01:04,610 --> 00:01:06,240
Guys, you're never gonna believe it.

26
00:01:06,290 --> 00:01:07,610
This headhunter called me.

27
00:01:07,660 --> 00:01:09,820
Gucci:著名意大利奢侈品品牌

28
00:01:07,660 --> 00:01:09,820
I have a meeting tomorrow with Gucci.

29
00:01:09,870 --> 00:01:11,630
Gucci wants me.

30
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:14,090
- I'm up for tenure. - Congratulations.

31
00:01:14,140 --> 00:01:15,920
You too. What are the odds?

32
00:01:16,970 --> 00:01:18,240
Guess what?

33
00:01:19,470 --> 00:01:21,890
I finally got that seed out of my teeth.

34
00:01:24,420 --> 00:01:26,110
I don't know who I'm happiest for.

35
00:01:26,160 --> 00:01:28,900
I do. He's been working on that all day.

36
00:01:30,900 --> 00:01:32,900
《老友记》第十季第十四集 "康斯薇拉公主"驾到

37
00:02:21,410 --> 00:02:23,340
Hey, Mon, was it weird

38
00:02:23,340 --> 00:02:25,530
changing your name to Geller Bing?

39
00:02:25,530 --> 00:02:28,970
No. No, it felt nice to acknowledge this.

40
00:02:29,140 --> 00:02:31,930
- Where'd you go to do it? - The--

41
00:02:31,980 --> 00:02:34,670
The Ministry of Names...

42
00:02:36,630 --> 00:02:37,510
...Bureau.

43
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,190
You never did it.

44
00:02:40,350 --> 00:02:42,820
I'm sorry. It's just the idea of--

45
00:02:42,870 --> 00:02:45,040
Of being an official Bing.

46
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,490
Hey, I will have you know that--

47
00:02:49,830 --> 00:02:51,980
Who am I kidding? Let's call the kid Geller

48
00:02:52,030 --> 00:02:53,540
and let Bing die with me.

49
00:02:55,570 --> 00:02:56,590
- Here you go. - Thanks.

50
00:02:56,770 --> 00:02:59,130
Honey, would you want me to take your name?

51
00:02:59,380 --> 00:03:00,110
Oh, it's up to you.

52
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:01,570
It's your name.

53
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:02,570
You've gotta live with it.

54
00:03:02,920 --> 00:03:04,970
Let's see. Call me Mrs. Hannigan.

55
00:03:05,020 --> 00:03:05,800
Mrs. Hannigan?

56
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:07,960
What? Can't you see I'm in the middle of something?

57
00:03:09,980 --> 00:03:11,030
I like it.

58
00:03:12,590 --> 00:03:14,440
- Hey, guys. - Hey, Joe.

59
00:03:14,490 --> 00:03:15,280
We've got a couple of things

60
00:03:15,330 --> 00:03:16,570
we've got to check out at the new house.

61
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:17,690
You want to come?

62
00:03:17,740 --> 00:03:18,900
No, thank you.

63
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:21,190
You're not happy about us moving...

64
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:23,030
...but you're the only one who hasn't seen the house.

65
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:24,000
Yeah, come with us.

66
00:03:24,050 --> 00:03:25,440
You'll see how close it is.

67
00:03:25,710 --> 00:03:27,340
No, it's not close.

68
00:03:27,390 --> 00:03:28,850
in escrow:根据协议由第三方保管  乔伊以为是地名

69
00:03:27,390 --> 00:03:28,850
You said it was in escrow.

70
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:30,920
I couldn't even find that on the map.

71
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:36,260
Joey, please come.

72
00:03:36,310 --> 00:03:37,870
It would mean so much to us.

73
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:40,980
You know what?

74
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:42,250
You are my friends.

75
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:43,280
I want to be supportive.

76
00:03:43,330 --> 00:03:44,760
I will come with you. Shotgun.

77
00:03:44,810 --> 00:03:45,630
Damn it.

78
00:03:46,350 --> 00:03:47,380
See you guys later.

79
00:03:47,430 --> 00:03:48,510
We'll pick you up at 11.

80
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,530
So glad you're coming.

81
00:03:49,580 --> 00:03:50,420
All right.

82
00:03:51,950 --> 00:03:52,890
Good for you.

83
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:53,970
That was really mature.

84
00:03:53,970 --> 00:03:55,910
What? No, the only reason I'm going...

85
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:57,350
...to their stupid house is

86
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,070
to point out everything wrong with it...

87
00:03:59,120 --> 00:03:59,860
...so they don't move.

88
00:03:59,910 --> 00:04:01,180
I'm gonna make them stay here.

89
00:04:01,690 --> 00:04:03,740
You're a strange kind of grownup.

90
00:04:06,190 --> 00:04:08,360
Joey, you can't make someone do something

91
00:04:08,410 --> 00:04:09,560
they don't want to do.

92
00:04:09,610 --> 00:04:10,290
Believe me.

93
00:04:10,340 --> 00:04:11,350
There's something I've been trying to

94
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:13,520
get Mike to do in bed, and--

95
00:04:15,130 --> 00:04:16,800
Can we not talk about that now?

96
00:04:16,850 --> 00:04:18,360
All right. Prude.

97
00:04:20,930 --> 00:04:22,550
Look, Monica and Chandler

98
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,860
really love this house.

99
00:04:23,910 --> 00:04:25,860
You are not gonna talk them into staying here.

100
00:04:25,910 --> 00:04:28,430
Hey, I can convince people to do anything, you know?

101
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:30,710
I bet I could even get Mike to do that thing.

102
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,520
What is it?

103
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:37,800
I am not gonna help you do that!

104
00:04:38,190 --> 00:04:39,430
Oh, my God.

105
00:04:46,310 --> 00:04:50,340
Hi. I'm here to see Mr. Campbell, with Gucci.

106
00:04:50,720 --> 00:04:53,450
The reservation's probably under Gucci.

107
00:04:53,570 --> 00:04:55,270
It's spelled like "Gukki"

108
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,330
which can be confusing.

109
00:04:58,050 --> 00:04:59,490
Mr.Campbell's not here yet.

110
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:01,160
Let me show you to his table.

111
00:05:05,130 --> 00:05:07,220
Oh, my God. That's my boss.

112
00:05:07,270 --> 00:05:08,350
You have to seat us somewhere else.

113
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:09,200
I'm sorry,

114
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:11,110
that's always Mr.Campbell's table.

115
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,910
But my boss cannot see me.

116
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:14,920
I'm interviewing for another job.

117
00:05:14,970 --> 00:05:17,480
I know. With "Gukki."

118
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:23,280
- Rachel? - I'm on a date.

119
00:05:24,570 --> 00:05:26,010
That's great.

120
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:27,320
Yeah, it is.

121
00:05:27,370 --> 00:05:28,830
Yeah, you know, it's tough.

122
00:05:28,830 --> 00:05:30,290
Single mom. Career.

123
00:05:30,340 --> 00:05:32,070
You gotta get out there.

124
00:05:33,310 --> 00:05:35,610
Well, you've got a good energy.

125
00:05:36,820 --> 00:05:38,280
- Rachel? - Yes, hi.

126
00:05:38,330 --> 00:05:39,750
- James Campbell. - Hi.

127
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:42,010
- Excuse us. - Please.

128
00:05:44,990 --> 00:05:46,800
He's cute.

129
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,060
So...

130
00:05:49,430 --> 00:05:51,890
...your resume is quite impressive.

131
00:05:54,460 --> 00:05:55,980
My resume?

132
00:05:56,290 --> 00:05:57,790
I wouldn't-- I wouldn't call

133
00:05:57,840 --> 00:06:01,290
my online dating profile a resume.

134
00:06:01,990 --> 00:06:03,110
Dating profile?

135
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:05,240
No, I'm-- I'm talking about the work resume.

136
00:06:08,940 --> 00:06:10,040
Whatever happened to

137
00:06:10,090 --> 00:06:12,250
just singing for no reason?

138
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:16,120
Maybe people found it weird.

139
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:19,360
So....

140
00:06:20,850 --> 00:06:22,730
Why do you want to leave Ralph Lauren?

141
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:23,440
What?

142
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:25,180
- I...I don't. - You don't?

143
00:06:25,230 --> 00:06:27,300
No, I love-- I love it there.

144
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:28,360
Well, if you don't want to leave,

145
00:06:28,410 --> 00:06:29,720
why are we having this lunch?

146
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:34,490
What?

147
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:38,730
Hugo Boss:德国奢侈品品牌

148
00:06:37,390 --> 00:06:38,730
That's Hugo Boss?

149
00:06:45,940 --> 00:06:47,820
This place is so depressing.

150
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:48,860
If I had to work here,

151
00:06:48,910 --> 00:06:49,810
I'd kill myself.

152
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:55,010
But you obviously haven't.

153
00:06:57,010 --> 00:06:58,110
How can I help you?

154
00:06:58,160 --> 00:07:00,090
I need to change my name, please.

155
00:07:00,140 --> 00:07:03,140
See, I need to change it because I'm hiding from the law.

156
00:07:06,020 --> 00:07:07,090
You're fun.

157
00:07:08,370 --> 00:07:09,780
You need to fill out this form.

158
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:11,150
Okay. Well, just so I know--

159
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,770
I don't know how it works. My name is Buffay...

160
00:07:13,820 --> 00:07:15,380
...and my husband's name is Hannigan.

161
00:07:15,430 --> 00:07:17,430
So is it supposed to be "Buffay-Hannigan"

162
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:18,610
or "Hannigan-Buffay"?

163
00:07:18,660 --> 00:07:20,310
It can be anything you want.

164
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:21,610
Well, not anything.

165
00:07:21,660 --> 00:07:23,630
Yeah. Anything.

166
00:07:25,370 --> 00:07:27,110
Oh, this could take a while.

167
00:07:29,300 --> 00:07:30,940
- Get out of my line. - Okay.

168
00:07:36,050 --> 00:07:37,930
- Hey. - Hey, Pheebs.

169
00:07:37,980 --> 00:07:40,500
Oh, not anymore. I changed it today.

170
00:07:40,550 --> 00:07:42,570
Oh, I'm sorry, Mrs. Hannigan.

171
00:07:42,620 --> 00:07:43,810
Wrong again.

172
00:07:46,110 --> 00:07:48,400
Apparently, you can change it to anything.

173
00:07:48,450 --> 00:07:49,240
So I thought, "All right,

174
00:07:49,290 --> 00:07:51,380
here's an opportunity to be creative."

175
00:07:51,730 --> 00:07:55,170
So meet Princess Consuela Banana Hammock.

176
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:03,990
That's what we were gonna name the baby.

177
00:08:06,870 --> 00:08:09,650
- Phoebe. - Princess Consuela.

178
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:13,370
You seriously changed your name to that?

179
00:08:13,420 --> 00:08:14,470
Okay, so from now on,

180
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:16,440
we have to call you Princess Consuela?

181
00:08:16,490 --> 00:08:19,250
No, I'm gonna have my friends call me Valerie.

182
00:08:23,770 --> 00:08:27,280
- Hey, how did the interview go? - Not good.

183
00:08:27,410 --> 00:08:29,440
You know. I always feel that way after an interview.

184
00:08:29,490 --> 00:08:31,350
I'll bet it went better than you think.

185
00:08:31,890 --> 00:08:34,080
Well, I didn't get the job at Gucci

186
00:08:34,130 --> 00:08:36,320
and I got fired from Ralph Lauren.

187
00:08:36,740 --> 00:08:38,240
That is a bad interview.

188
00:08:39,340 --> 00:08:41,000
What are you talking about?

189
00:08:41,050 --> 00:08:41,920
How did this happen?

190
00:08:41,970 --> 00:08:44,710
My boss was at the same restaurant

191
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:46,240
where I was having my interview...

192
00:08:46,290 --> 00:08:47,620
...and he heard everything.

193
00:08:47,670 --> 00:08:49,400
Later, he calls me into his office

194
00:08:49,450 --> 00:08:51,560
and tells me he'll have to let me go...

195
00:08:51,610 --> 00:08:53,430
...because I'm not a team player.

196
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:55,350
And I said, "Wait a minute. Yes, I am."

197
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:58,380
And then I had to sit there for 45 minutes...

198
00:08:58,430 --> 00:09:02,340
...while he proved that that, in fact, was true.

199
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:05,900
Oh, God, I'm so sorry.

200
00:09:07,420 --> 00:09:08,370
Hey.

201
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:11,300
What--? What's this?

202
00:09:12,230 --> 00:09:14,510
Why, it's a bottle of champagne.

203
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:16,190
Why is this here?

204
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:18,370
- Ross. - I guess it's here...

205
00:09:18,420 --> 00:09:19,740
...because I got tenure!

206
00:09:19,790 --> 00:09:21,690
- Congratulations. - Congratulations.

207
00:09:21,740 --> 00:09:25,120
This is the single greatest day of my professional career.

208
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:27,550
- Gunther. Six glasses. - Six?

209
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:28,880
You want me to join you?

210
00:09:28,930 --> 00:09:30,200
I thought Joey was here.

211
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:31,020
Five is good.

212
00:09:34,970 --> 00:09:37,470
Wow, I'm gonna have a loogey in my coffee tomorrow.

213
00:09:39,310 --> 00:09:41,250
Israeli champagne.

214
00:09:41,940 --> 00:09:43,380
And it's vanilla.

215
00:09:44,670 --> 00:09:46,940
I got tenure. I didn't win the lottery.

216
00:09:48,260 --> 00:09:50,580
Hey, Rach, so how did your thing go?

217
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:51,730
Good.

218
00:09:51,780 --> 00:09:54,050
But I'm not going to hear about that for a couple days.

219
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,800
Oh, you know what, you're gonna get it.

220
00:09:55,850 --> 00:09:57,260
I can feel it.

221
00:09:57,310 --> 00:09:58,320
Can you?

222
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:01,390
All right, everybody, here's to Ross.

223
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:06,480
And to years of hard work finally paying off.

224
00:10:06,530 --> 00:10:09,180
And to knowing that your career

225
00:10:09,230 --> 00:10:10,840
doesn't mean everything.

226
00:10:10,890 --> 00:10:13,990
But also knowing it means a lot.

227
00:10:15,410 --> 00:10:18,110
But more importantly, to full, well-rounded lives.

228
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:19,770
That center around work.

229
00:10:20,030 --> 00:10:22,110
- To Ross. - To Ross.

230
00:10:26,170 --> 00:10:28,090
You know what the best part about this is?

231
00:10:28,140 --> 00:10:29,620
I can never be fired.

232
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:31,200
- Oh, God. - No, seriously.

233
00:10:31,250 --> 00:10:34,030
I have job security for life.

234
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:36,340
You know? I mean, I never have to worry.

235
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:39,700
Oh, look at you. Look how happy you are for me.

236
00:10:42,380 --> 00:10:46,080
No, it's not that. I got fired today.

237
00:10:46,130 --> 00:10:48,230
And I didn't get the other job.

238
00:10:51,630 --> 00:10:53,890
Rach, I'm so sorry.

239
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,560
Great, I feel like an idiot.

240
00:10:56,610 --> 00:10:58,250
No, it's okay. You didn't know.

241
00:11:00,430 --> 00:11:02,090
Little heads-up would've been nice.

242
00:11:11,810 --> 00:11:13,550
Thank you for letting us see the house again.

243
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:16,360
And thank you for explaining to us what escrow means.

244
00:11:16,410 --> 00:11:17,890
I've already forgotten what you said,

245
00:11:17,940 --> 00:11:18,770
but thank you.

246
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:21,170
Take as long as you want.

247
00:11:21,220 --> 00:11:22,690
Just let me know when you're through.

248
00:11:25,620 --> 00:11:27,030
So glad you decided to come.

249
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:29,010
Me too. Yeah, this place is great.

250
00:11:29,060 --> 00:11:30,730
So happy for you guys.

251
00:11:30,780 --> 00:11:33,010
Although, you know, I hope you like fungus.

252
00:11:35,330 --> 00:11:36,590
- What? - Fungus.

253
00:11:36,930 --> 00:11:38,320
Yeah. Place is full of it.

254
00:11:39,130 --> 00:11:40,240
No, it's not.

255
00:11:40,290 --> 00:11:41,220
We had an inspection

256
00:11:41,270 --> 00:11:42,270
and they didn't find anything.

257
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:44,520
Okay. Then I guess I have dry eyes

258
00:11:44,570 --> 00:11:45,880
and a scratchy throat for no reason.

259
00:11:45,930 --> 00:11:47,460
Maybe it's because you hung your head

260
00:11:47,510 --> 00:11:49,030
out the window like a dog...

261
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:50,820
...the whole ride here.

262
00:11:52,760 --> 00:11:53,770
Maybe.

263
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,370
So this is the living room, huh?

264
00:11:56,510 --> 00:11:58,150
It's pretty dark.

265
00:12:02,350 --> 00:12:03,640
No, it's not.

266
00:12:03,690 --> 00:12:04,720
Are you kidding?

267
00:12:04,770 --> 00:12:07,210
I think I just saw a bat in the corner.

268
00:12:08,090 --> 00:12:09,740
When your head was hanging out the window,

269
00:12:09,790 --> 00:12:12,000
it didn't hit a mailbox, did it?

270
00:12:13,730 --> 00:12:14,790
Maybe.

271
00:12:16,350 --> 00:12:17,890
Look, I just think you guys can do

272
00:12:17,940 --> 00:12:19,700
better than this house, you know?

273
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:21,980
Or any other house for that matter.

274
00:12:22,030 --> 00:12:23,190
Oh, Joey.

275
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:25,780
We know you're having a hard time with this, but we--

276
00:12:25,830 --> 00:12:26,860
We love it here.

277
00:12:26,910 --> 00:12:28,730
Fine! Ok. If you love this house so much...

278
00:12:28,780 --> 00:12:30,400
...you should live here. Okay?

279
00:12:30,450 --> 00:12:32,820
I hope you get used to that weird humming sound.

280
00:12:34,870 --> 00:12:37,260
- Joey, we know that's you. - No...

281
00:12:37,310 --> 00:12:38,740
...it's not.

282
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:47,210
- Welcome back. - I missed you.

283
00:12:47,260 --> 00:12:49,220
- Oh, me too. - So, what's new?

284
00:12:49,380 --> 00:12:51,850
Well, I am no longer Phoebe Buffay.

285
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:53,500
That's great. You changed your name?

286
00:12:53,550 --> 00:12:54,460
Yes, I did.

287
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:58,050
Meet Princess Consuela Banana Hammock.

288
00:13:00,470 --> 00:13:02,220
- You're kidding, right? - Nope.

289
00:13:02,850 --> 00:13:04,330
- You really did that? - Yep.

290
00:13:04,990 --> 00:13:06,740
You can't do that.

291
00:13:07,190 --> 00:13:08,280
Why?

292
00:13:08,450 --> 00:13:09,650
Why? It's fun.

293
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:12,040
It's different. No one else has a name like it.

294
00:13:13,760 --> 00:13:15,290
Then I'm gonna change my name.

295
00:13:15,340 --> 00:13:17,670
Great. Okay, what are you gonna change it to?

296
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,190
Crap Bag.

297
00:13:21,340 --> 00:13:22,750
Mike Crap Bag?

298
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:25,330
No. No "Mike." No, just "Crap Bag."

299
00:13:25,380 --> 00:13:27,340
First name: Crap. Last name: Bag.

300
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:30,120
You're not serious, right?

301
00:13:30,170 --> 00:13:31,160
Yeah, I'm serious.

302
00:13:31,210 --> 00:13:32,430
It's fun, it's different,

303
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:34,100
and no one else has a name like that.

304
00:13:34,930 --> 00:13:36,650
Well, then great.

305
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:38,600
If you love it, I love it.

306
00:13:38,650 --> 00:13:40,320
I do love it. And I love your name.

307
00:13:40,370 --> 00:13:41,670
I love Princess Consuela.

308
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:43,330
And I love Crap.

309
00:13:53,540 --> 00:13:56,540
- Who are you? - Oh, hi. I'm Joey.

310
00:13:56,590 --> 00:13:58,770
My stupid friends are buying this house.

311
00:13:58,820 --> 00:13:59,460
Who are you?

312
00:13:59,510 --> 00:14:00,790
I'm Mackenzie.

313
00:14:01,450 --> 00:14:03,630
My stupid parents are selling this house.

314
00:14:05,690 --> 00:14:07,090
I hate my parents.

315
00:14:07,550 --> 00:14:09,370
I hate my friends.

316
00:14:12,780 --> 00:14:14,370
Look, there's gotta be a way

317
00:14:14,420 --> 00:14:15,970
that we can stop this from happening.

318
00:14:16,360 --> 00:14:17,300
Like what?

319
00:14:20,140 --> 00:14:23,590
Okay, you come with me and you tell them that the house is haunted.

320
00:14:23,940 --> 00:14:25,480
What are you, 8?

321
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:31,310
Okay. Let's hear your great idea.

322
00:14:31,360 --> 00:14:33,070
I don't have any great ideas.

323
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:34,360
I am 8.

324
00:14:37,490 --> 00:14:39,490
There's gotta be a way. I mean, you know...

325
00:14:39,540 --> 00:14:41,250
...if Monica and Chandler move here,

326
00:14:41,300 --> 00:14:42,990
and Phoebe's married to Mike...

327
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:44,880
...that just leaves me and Ross and Rach.

328
00:14:44,930 --> 00:14:46,060
You know what I mean?

329
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:48,420
I really don't.

330
00:14:49,950 --> 00:14:51,210
What am I gonna do?

331
00:14:51,260 --> 00:14:53,190
I feel like I'm losing my friends.

332
00:14:53,470 --> 00:14:55,370
My parents say I'll make new friends.

333
00:14:55,420 --> 00:14:57,010
Yeah, sure, easy for you.

334
00:14:57,060 --> 00:14:59,460
You're young. Me? I'm set in my ways.

335
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:03,740
This is what my mom was talking about.

336
00:15:03,790 --> 00:15:05,490
Whiners are wieners.

337
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:11,730
Look, you want your friends to be happy, right?

338
00:15:13,040 --> 00:15:15,440
Yeah. Yeah, I guess. Yeah.

339
00:15:15,910 --> 00:15:18,000
Well, if moving here is gonna make them happy,

340
00:15:18,050 --> 00:15:19,730
don't you want them to do it?

341
00:15:20,650 --> 00:15:22,830
Yeah. Maybe.

342
00:15:24,330 --> 00:15:26,150
Then you've gotta let them go.

343
00:15:31,850 --> 00:15:33,820
Oh, I hate to admit it, but you're--

344
00:15:34,420 --> 00:15:36,200
You're probably right.

345
00:15:37,190 --> 00:15:38,890
How'd you get to be so smart?

346
00:15:40,150 --> 00:15:41,210
I read a lot.

347
00:15:43,130 --> 00:15:45,140
Just when I thought we could be friends.

348
00:15:49,110 --> 00:15:52,200
Oh, hey, Rach. I just heard. I'm so sorry.

349
00:15:52,410 --> 00:15:54,260
Oh, thank you....

350
00:15:54,990 --> 00:15:56,860
You still don't know my name, do you?

351
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:00,300
Well, now I don't have to.

352
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:07,750
Ross, what is taking you so long?

353
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:16,960
I'm sorry. It's almost as if

354
00:16:17,010 --> 00:16:19,550
this wasn't built for a quick getaway.

355
00:16:22,310 --> 00:16:23,350
Rachel?

356
00:16:24,410 --> 00:16:27,130
Mark? Oh, my God.

357
00:16:27,250 --> 00:16:28,240
How have you been?

358
00:16:28,290 --> 00:16:31,170
Fantastic. You remember Ross.

359
00:16:31,220 --> 00:16:32,950
Sure.

360
00:16:33,460 --> 00:16:34,720
What's with the chair?

361
00:16:37,030 --> 00:16:38,370
You know, you can't always

362
00:16:38,420 --> 00:16:40,500
get a seat on the subway, so....

363
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:43,480
Clever.

364
00:16:44,380 --> 00:16:45,570
So how are you?

365
00:16:45,620 --> 00:16:48,490
You're not catching me on my best day.

366
00:16:48,540 --> 00:16:51,640
Yeah, a box full of your desk stuff doesn't say "big promotion."

367
00:16:51,690 --> 00:16:53,070
No, but it's good.

368
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:55,510
You know, I'm gonna take some time off...

369
00:16:55,560 --> 00:16:57,260
- ...and do charity work. - Are you sure?

370
00:16:57,310 --> 00:16:59,430
We may have something at Louis Vuitton.

371
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:01,620
Screw charity work. What do you got?

372
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:04,390
Why don't we have dinner and talk?

373
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:07,090
- Great. I'll call you. - Okay.

374
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:08,340
Nice to see you again.

375
00:17:08,390 --> 00:17:10,150
Yeah. Yeah. I got tenure.

376
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:17,760
Oh, my God.

377
00:17:17,810 --> 00:17:20,690
See? I told you something good would come along.

378
00:17:20,740 --> 00:17:22,140
And he seemed really nice.

379
00:17:22,190 --> 00:17:23,890
I've met him before?

380
00:17:23,940 --> 00:17:26,100
Ross, that's Mark.

381
00:17:26,150 --> 00:17:27,470
From Bloomingdale's?

382
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:29,720
You were insanely jealous of him.

383
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,710
- That is Mark? - Yes.

384
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:33,590
I hate that guy.

385
00:17:34,590 --> 00:17:35,910
No, no, no.

386
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:37,430
You cannot go to dinner with him.

387
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:39,240
What? You don't want me to get a job?

388
00:17:39,290 --> 00:17:41,210
Yeah, I'm sure he'll give you a job.

389
00:17:41,260 --> 00:17:43,320
Maybe make you his "sex-cretary."

390
00:17:44,300 --> 00:17:47,100
I'm serious. I just don't trust that guy, okay?

391
00:17:47,150 --> 00:17:48,270
Ross. You know what--?

392
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:50,560
Okay, let's talk about it later. There comes security.

393
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,670
Oh, I love this street.

394
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:08,690
The trees and the big front yards and the actual picket fences.

395
00:18:09,030 --> 00:18:11,400
Man, those two dogs are going at it.

396
00:18:15,370 --> 00:18:16,770
Hey. Where you been?

397
00:18:16,820 --> 00:18:18,870
Oh, just, you know, looking around.

398
00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:19,880
But you know what?

399
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:22,800
This house is great.

400
00:18:22,890 --> 00:18:24,750
Really? What changed your mind?

401
00:18:24,850 --> 00:18:28,580
The little girl who lives here made me feel better about the whole thing.

402
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:31,680
Joey? There was a little girl who lived here,

403
00:18:31,730 --> 00:18:33,570
but she died, like, 30 years ago.

404
00:18:38,940 --> 00:18:39,920
What?

405
00:18:40,950 --> 00:18:43,010
I'm just messing with you.

406
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:45,740
That's not funny.

407
00:18:45,790 --> 00:18:47,860
You know I'm afraid of little-girl ghosts.

408
00:18:48,530 --> 00:18:50,770
Now that you're okay with the house,

409
00:18:50,820 --> 00:18:52,040
do you want to go see your room?

410
00:18:52,910 --> 00:18:53,790
What?

411
00:18:54,170 --> 00:18:55,280
I get my own room?

412
00:18:56,460 --> 00:18:57,760
You don't think we'd buy a house

413
00:18:57,810 --> 00:18:59,580
and not have a Joey room, do you?

414
00:19:00,340 --> 00:19:02,030
Oh, my God.

415
00:19:05,140 --> 00:19:06,840
Hey, can I have an aquarium?

416
00:19:06,890 --> 00:19:08,120
And a sex swing?

417
00:19:10,250 --> 00:19:11,190
No.

418
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:13,890
Why not? I'll keep the tank clean.

419
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:19,110
After you, Ms. Bananahammock.

420
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:20,740
Thank you, Mr. Bag.

421
00:19:22,250 --> 00:19:24,690
- Oh, hi, Rita. - How are you?

422
00:19:24,740 --> 00:19:27,120
Good. Oh, Rita's a massage client.

423
00:19:27,170 --> 00:19:28,010
Yeah.

424
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:30,160
Why don't you introduce me?

425
00:19:33,070 --> 00:19:34,790
Rita, this is my husband.

426
00:19:35,770 --> 00:19:37,770
Why don't you tell her my name?

427
00:19:39,180 --> 00:19:43,810
Okay, I will. This is-- This is my husband, Crap Bag.

428
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:47,080
Crap Bag?

429
00:19:47,180 --> 00:19:49,050
If you need an easy way to remember it,

430
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:51,380
just think of a bag of crap.

431
00:19:53,930 --> 00:19:56,850
- Okay. Excuse me. - Yeah.

432
00:19:59,720 --> 00:20:01,610
Okay, fine, you made your point.

433
00:20:01,660 --> 00:20:03,720
Can you please just be Mike Hannigan again?

434
00:20:03,770 --> 00:20:05,620
Only if you'll be Phoebe Buffay.

435
00:20:07,180 --> 00:20:09,960
How about--? How about Buffay-Hannigan?

436
00:20:10,200 --> 00:20:11,060
Really?

437
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:11,980
Yeah.

438
00:20:12,030 --> 00:20:15,010
I'm Phoebe Buffay-Hannigan-Banana Hammock.

439
00:20:17,410 --> 00:20:19,600
Do you even know what a banana hammock is?

440
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:21,330
It's a funny word.

441
00:20:21,590 --> 00:20:22,850
It's a Speedo.

442
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:28,960
Oh, crap.

443
00:20:32,950 --> 00:20:35,130
- Hey, is Rachel here? - Nope.

444
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:37,200
She's still at dinner?

445
00:20:37,740 --> 00:20:39,290
I guess. Why, who's she with?

446
00:20:39,290 --> 00:20:40,370
That guy, Mark...

447
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:41,670
...from Bloomingdale's.

448
00:20:41,720 --> 00:20:43,750
She thinks he's just being nice to her.

449
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:45,550
But I know he really wants to sleep with her.

450
00:20:45,830 --> 00:20:47,430
It's seven years ago.

451
00:20:49,850 --> 00:20:51,560
My time machine works.

452
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:55,800
We ran into him on the street today,

453
00:20:55,850 --> 00:20:57,290
and he said he might have a job for her.

454
00:20:57,340 --> 00:20:59,560
But I know he just wants to get into her pants.

455
00:21:00,900 --> 00:21:02,470
So, what if he wants to sleep with her?

456
00:21:02,520 --> 00:21:04,930
I mean, she's single, and he's cute.

457
00:21:05,100 --> 00:21:06,310
Excuse me?

458
00:21:07,170 --> 00:21:08,430
Oh, please.

459
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:11,320
Yesterday, on the subway, you couldn't stop staring...

460
00:21:11,370 --> 00:21:13,410
...at that woman with the big breasts the whole time.

461
00:21:13,460 --> 00:21:16,500
For your information, I was staring at her baby.

462
00:21:16,550 --> 00:21:18,320
We're about to be parents.

463
00:21:19,170 --> 00:21:20,780
Oh, sorry.

464
00:21:31,230 --> 00:21:34,280
- Hi, you guys. - Hi. So...

465
00:21:34,330 --> 00:21:35,540
...how was dinner?

466
00:21:35,590 --> 00:21:38,100
Oh, it was great. Mark is so sweet.

467
00:21:38,150 --> 00:21:40,070
Oh, yeah? Yeah, I wonder why?

468
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:42,190
What could that smarmy letch possibly want?

469
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:45,720
Oh, Ross. Come on. He is happily married.

470
00:21:45,770 --> 00:21:47,450
His wife just had twins.

471
00:21:47,970 --> 00:21:49,450
Should we send something?

472
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:52,590
How did the job stuff go?

473
00:21:53,780 --> 00:21:55,580
He offered me one.

474
00:21:56,420 --> 00:21:58,510
- That's great. - Congratulations.

475
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:00,740
I know, it's amazing.

476
00:22:01,300 --> 00:22:02,840
It's amazing. It's so much better

477
00:22:02,890 --> 00:22:04,840
than what I had at Ralph Lauren.

478
00:22:04,890 --> 00:22:07,570
- The money is great. - Can we--?

479
00:22:07,620 --> 00:22:08,980
Can we just stop for a second?

480
00:22:09,070 --> 00:22:12,210
Who said something better would come along?

481
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:13,320
You didn't believe me.

482
00:22:13,370 --> 00:22:15,520
I told you everything was gonna work out.

483
00:22:15,790 --> 00:22:16,570
You know what?

484
00:22:16,620 --> 00:22:18,800
This calls for a bottle of lsrael's finest.

485
00:22:23,210 --> 00:22:25,130
The job is in Paris.

486
00:22:38,280 --> 00:22:41,350
I mean, this soap opera is a great gig...

487
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:43,230
...but am I missing opportunities?

488
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:46,140
You know, I've always thought of myself as a serious actor.

489
00:22:46,310 --> 00:22:48,890
Should I be trying to do more independent movies?

490
00:22:49,460 --> 00:22:50,640
I don't know.

491
00:22:52,220 --> 00:22:53,630
But you know what?

492
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:55,560
I'm gonna put you on with my bear.

493
00:22:55,610 --> 00:22:56,620
Hold on.

494
00:22:58,470 --> 00:23:00,360
Hey, Bailey, I need some career advice.

